text: Cloacal swab samples were obtained from 10 healthy and clinically sound Eclectus parrots (E. roratus), which belong to a bird breeder in Bogor, West Java, Indonesia. Swabs were stored in viral transport media containing phosphate-buffered saline, penicillin (1000 IU/ml), and streptomycin (10 mg/ml). Samples were carried in a cooler box during transportation and stored at −80°C until use. All birds had never been vaccinated. The IBV vaccine strain H120 was used as a positive control.
